[SkillPath "practice_deals/100_miscellaneous"]
[Student "S"]
{You respond with your 5-card Major, 1\S.

Partner jumps to 3\H.  

With partner's 16-18 points you probably have enough strength for game.

With partner's six \Hs you have an 8-card fit.

So you bid 4\H.

West would play 4\H.

Click 

East plays 4\H. South leads \CA, \CK, \C4. North plays \C8 then \C2.

<b>East plays 4\H. South leads \CA, \CK, \C4. North plays \C8 then \C2.</b>

Losers: \S 0 : \H 0 : \D 1 : \C 3 : Total = 4

Suppose you discard a \D from dummy. If North doesn't ruff this \Cthen your \CQ will win. You could then try to establish dummy's \DQ to discard your fourth \C on. 

But you know that plan won't work because North <b>IS</b> going to ruff this \C if you discard. You only have one chance to make this contract, and that is the chance that North was not dealt the \HJ. So you ruff with dummy's \H10 and pray North doesn't over-ruff.

The prayer was answered, North did not hold the \HJ. 

So you won that trick and still had your \CQ to use after you pulled trumps.}
[Play "W"]CA

